714020f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, east side, from 59th to 58th Streets. The New York
Athletic Club is on the S.E. corner of 59th Street, and the
Coronet, an apartment house is on the N.E. corner of 58th Street.
The Athletic Club will soon be demolished to erect the Hotel St.
Moritz, but the Coronet will still stand in 1935.
June, 1925.

718425f-a.text:
Central Park South (West 59th Street ), south side,
west from a point (No. 126-30, the new 15 story apartment
house at left margin that replaced the former 8 story
Hawthorne) between Sixth and Seventh Avenues, and to the
latter (right). Under construction there is the new N.Y.
Athletic Club occupying the former sites of 2 of the old
"Spanish Flats", the Madrid and the Lisbon. The Cordova
and the Granada (45 story, Essex House erected here prior
to 1934)are still standing while to the left is a cleared
space where the Valencia stood (present site of the 36
story Hampshire House). Across the latter feature appears
a corner of the rear of the Salamanca which faces on W. 58th
Street. In 1930 this site was completely vacant.
The photographer is viewing southwestward from the "Cliffs"
of Central Park.
May 25, 1928.
P.L. Sperr

714022f-a.text:
New York Athletic Club, 59th Street at S.E. corner of Sixth Avenue. This will soon be demolished for the construction of the Hotel St. Moritz, while the new Athletic Club building will replace the Spanish Flats, on the S.E. corner of Seventh Avenue and 59th Street.
May 25, 1928.
P.L. Sperr.
